Your project is set up correctly. Run tests in hot-reload mode with:

```
dotnet test --hotreload
```

This keeps the test host running. When you save changes to `EmailValidatorTests.cs` (e.g., fixing `IsValidEmail` to actually check for `@`), tests automatically re-run **without a full rebuild** — much faster iteration.

Right now `Validate_MissingAtSign_ReturnsFalse` will fail because `IsValidEmail` only checks for null/empty. You'd fix it by updating the method, e.g.:

```csharp
private static bool IsValidEmail(string email)
{
    return !string.IsNullOrEmpty(email) && email.Contains('@');
}
```

Save the file and hot reload will re-execute the tests instantly.
